The African National Congress (ANC) will on Saturday host its annual January 8 statement with an anniversary rally in Polokwane. Party president Cyril Ramaphosa will deliver the January 8 Statement during the celebrations that will take place at the Peter Mokaba Stadium. The January 8 Statement paves way for the party’s plans for the year and provides a broad framework with the country’s president ahead of his State of the Nation Address next month. Below is a list of some of the 2021 priorities the ANC made during its January 8 Statement: Restoring the economy to growth and creating jobs Our country’s energy security remains a priority Tackling poverty and improving people’s lives Education and skills for a changing world Safe and secure communities Accelerated land redistribution and rural development Forging ahead with the renewal of the ANC National General Council that enhances renewal and unity Achieve a decisive mandate in local government elections